rComments: He makes simple things hard. He uses jargons to make him appear knowledgeable, but actually he is not. Homework as well as lectures not concise and clear. Make you memorize things instead of understand them. He doesn't understand education! His exam is full of computation questions which are just brute force and meaningless. Worst guy ever !
Caring prof, and good lecturer. The only issue is that if you did not do a question well on the midterm, and you asked the professor what went wrong, he may have trouble explaining it concretely.
Solid prof; solid course content. It is during this course when you realize why Fourier transform in calculus class can be useful.
An excellent Prof!really knows his stuff andis not afraid to try unconventional methods to help his students grasp concepts
Explains well, clear notes, the pace is kinda fast tho.
Wonderful guy - fantastic professor, extremely intelligent, and cares for students - really goes the extra mile. Fantastic.
